@Ldpe2G 
This might because ps-lite in the git submodule is not update to date with https://github.com/dmlc/ps-lite. The git submodule is on (7faaeb73bcb9d68b464186d3191494aa95243703) while the [ps-lite master](https://github.com/dmlc/ps-lite) is on (8aff164580f0e4ff81ad98038b6ec4ec02452ce8)

Just update ps-lite by pulling from the master branch can solve this problem

@pluskid , it is not data-par . I  mean that : 

Assume that the system works on two gpus(gpu0,gpu1), we according to the following steps to create a network: 
1. Splitting  layer1 into two parts, one part binds on gpu0, and another part binds on gpu1; 
2. Splitting  layer2 into two parts, one part binds on gpu0, and another part binds on gpu1;
3. Doing the same  action with the rest of layers.

(As far as i know , the current mxnet implements the model-par by binding the whole layer1 on gpu0, and binding the whole layer2 on gpu1.)
